{
  "info": {
    "name": "AgentAuth MCP Server",
    "description": "Tests the AgentAuth MCP endpoint (Streamable HTTP at /mcp) and the REST API endpoints that back the MCP tools.\n\nUsage:\n1. Set the `base_url` variable to your AgentAuth instance (e.g. http://localhost:8000)\n2. Start with the **MCP Protocol** folder to test the /mcp endpoint directly via JSON-RPC 2.0\n3. Or use the **REST API** folders to test the underlying HTTP endpoints\n4. Run `Quickstart` (in either folder) to register an agent and auto-populate collection variables",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "mcp_session_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "api_key", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "agent_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "credential_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "delegation_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "MCP Protocol",
      "description": "Tests the MCP Streamable HTTP endpoint at /mcp using JSON-RPC 2.0.\n\nRun these in order:\n1. Initialize — starts a session\n2. List Tools — shows available MCP tools\n3. Call any tool (discover, quickstart, authenticate, etc.)\n\nThe Mcp-Session-Id header is auto-populated from the Initialize response.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Initialize Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "// Save session ID from response header",
                  "const sessionId = pm.response.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id');",
                  "if (sessionId) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('mcp_session_id', sessionId);",
                  "    pm.test('Has Mcp-Session-Id header', () => pm.expect(sessionId).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "// Handle SSE or JSON response",
                  "const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
                  "if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.test('Returns initialize result', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.result).to.have.property('serverInfo');",
                  "        pm.expect(json.result).to.have.property('protocolVersion');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"method\": \"initialize\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"protocolVersion\": \"2025-03-26\",\n    \"capabilities\": {},\n    \"clientInfo\": {\n      \"name\": \"postman\",\n      \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Initializes an MCP session. The response includes server info, capabilities, and a session ID (Mcp-Session-Id header) that must be included in all subsequent requests."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Send Initialized Notification",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 202 or 204', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 202, 204]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"notifications/initialized\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Sends the initialized notification to complete the MCP handshake. This is a JSON-RPC notification (no id field, no response expected)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. List Tools",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
                  "if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.test('Returns tools array', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.result).to.have.property('tools');",
                  "        pm.expect(json.result.tools).to.be.an('array');",
                  "        pm.expect(json.result.tools.length).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('Has discover tool', () => {",
                  "        const names = json.result.tools.map(t => t.name);",
                  "        pm.expect(names).to.include('discover');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 2,\n  \"method\": \"tools/list\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all available MCP tools. Returns tool names, descriptions, and input schemas."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Call: discover",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 3,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"discover\",\n    \"arguments\": {}\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Calls the `discover` tool via MCP. Returns AgentAuth service metadata (issuer, grant types, scopes, endpoints)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Call: quickstart",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
                  "if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (json.result && json.result.content) {",
                  "        try {",
                  "            const data = JSON.parse(json.result.content[0].text);",
                  "            if (data.agent?.id)      pm.collectionVariables.set('agent_id', data.agent.id);",
                  "            if (data.api_key)        pm.collectionVariables.set('api_key', data.api_key);",
                  "            if (data.access_token)   pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "            if (data.refresh_token)  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', data.refresh_token);",
                  "        } catch(e) {}",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 4,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"quickstart\",\n    \"arguments\": {\n      \"name\": \"postman-mcp-agent\",\n      \"agent_type\": \"orchestrator\",\n      \"description\": \"Created via MCP protocol in Postman\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Calls the `quickstart` tool via MCP. Registers a new agent and returns credentials. Auto-populates agent_id, api_key, access_token, and refresh_token variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Call: authenticate",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const contentType = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '';",
                  "if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (json.result && json.result.content) {",
                  "        try {",
                  "            const data = JSON.parse(json.result.content[0].text);",
                  "            if (data.access_token)   pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', data.access_token);",
                  "            if (data.refresh_token)  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', data.refresh_token);",
                  "        } catch(e) {}",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 5,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"authenticate\",\n    \"arguments\": {\n      \"api_key\": \"{{api_key}}\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Calls the `authenticate` tool via MCP. Exchanges an API key for an access token. Updates access_token and refresh_token variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Call: list_agents",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 6,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"list_agents\",\n    \"arguments\": {\n      \"access_token\": \"{{access_token}}\",\n      \"limit\": 10\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Calls the `list_agents` tool via MCP. Lists registered agents using the access token from a previous authenticate or quickstart call."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Call: introspect_token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" },
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"id\": 7,\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"name\": \"introspect_token\",\n    \"arguments\": {\n      \"token\": \"{{access_token}}\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Calls the `introspect_token` tool via MCP. Checks whether a token is valid and returns its claims."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Terminate Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 204 or 405', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 204, 405]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Mcp-Session-Id", "value": "{{mcp_session_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Terminates the MCP session. After this, the Mcp-Session-Id is no longer valid and a new Initialize is required."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Discovery",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Discover Service Configuration",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Has issuer', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('issuer');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/.well-known/agent-configuration",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [".well-known", "agent-configuration"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `discover()` — Returns service metadata: issuer, grant types, supported scopes, token lifetimes and endpoint URLs."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Agent Lifecycle",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Quickstart (Register Agent)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 201', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Returns agent + api_key + access_token', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('agent');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('api_key');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.agent?.id)      pm.collectionVariables.set('agent_id', json.agent.id);",
                  "if (json.api_key)        pm.collectionVariables.set('api_key', json.api_key);",
                  "if (json.access_token)   pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "if (json.refresh_token)  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"postman-test-agent\",\n  \"agent_type\": \"orchestrator\",\n  \"description\": \"Created by Postman collection test\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/agents/quickstart",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "agents", "quickstart"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `quickstart()` — Registers a new root agent and returns credentials in one call. The raw `api_key` is only shown here; store it securely. Automatically sets `agent_id`, `api_key`, `access_token`, and `refresh_token` collection variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Agents",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response has data array', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('data');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/agents?limit=50&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "agents"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "offset", "value": "0" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `list_agents()` — Lists all registered agents with pagination support."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Agent",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns agent with id', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/agents/{{agent_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "agents", "{{agent_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `get_agent()` — Fetches full details for a specific agent by UUID."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Authentication & Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Authenticate (client_credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns access_token', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token_type.toLowerCase()).to.equal('bearer');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token)  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "if (json.refresh_token) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"client_credentials\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"{{api_key}}\",\n  \"scope\": \"api.read agents.write\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `authenticate()` — Exchanges an API key for an access token via the OAuth 2.0 client_credentials grant. Updates `access_token` and `refresh_token` collection variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns new access_token and refresh_token', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('refresh_token');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token)  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "if (json.refresh_token) pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"grant_type\": \"refresh_token\",\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `refresh_token()` — Exchanges a refresh token for a new access + refresh token pair. Updates both collection variables."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Introspect Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns active boolean', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('active');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.active).to.be.a('boolean');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token/introspect",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "token", "introspect"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `introspect_token()` — RFC 7662 token introspection. Returns `active: true/false` plus decoded claims (sub, scopes, agent_type, trust_level, exp) if active."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 204', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 204]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/token/revoke",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "token", "revoke"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `revoke_token()` — RFC 7009 token revocation. Works for both access and refresh tokens. After calling this, re-authenticate to get a fresh token."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Credentials (API Keys)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Credential",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 201', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Returns credential with id and raw_key', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('raw_key');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('credential_id', json.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"agent_id\": \"{{agent_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"api_key\",\n  \"scopes\": [\"api.read\"]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/credentials",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "credentials"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `create_credential()` — Issues a new API key for an agent. The `raw_key` is returned only once; store it securely. Sets the `credential_id` collection variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Rotate Credential",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 201', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Returns new credential with raw_key', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('raw_key');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('credential_id', json.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/credentials/{{credential_id}}/rotate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "credentials", "{{credential_id}}", "rotate"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `rotate_credential()` — Revokes the existing API key and issues a new one atomically. Updates `credential_id` with the new credential UUID."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke Credential",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 204', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 204]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/credentials/{{credential_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "credentials", "{{credential_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `revoke_credential()` — Permanently revokes an API key. This is irreversible."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Delegation",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Delegation",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 or 201', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Returns delegation with id', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('delegation_id', json.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"delegate_agent_id\": \"{{agent_id}}\",\n  \"scopes\": [\"api.read\"],\n  \"max_chain_depth\": 3,\n  \"expires_at\": \"2027-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/delegations",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "delegations"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `create_delegation()` — Delegates a subset of the caller's permissions to another agent. `scopes` must be a subset of the delegating agent's own scopes. Sets `delegation_id`.\n\nNote: update `delegate_agent_id` with a different agent's UUID in a real test scenario."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "REST: Authorization",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check Permission",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns allowed boolean', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('allowed');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.allowed).to.be.a('boolean');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"agent_id\": \"{{agent_id}}\",\n  \"action\": \"read\",\n  \"resource\": \"/api/v1/credentials\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/policies/evaluate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "policies", "evaluate"]
            },
            "description": "MCP tool: `check_permission()` — Dry-run policy evaluation. Returns `{ allowed: bool, effect: 'allow'|'deny' }` without actually performing the action. Valid `action` values: `read`, `write`, `delete`, `execute`, `delegate`, `admin`."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
